cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.AR, cs.SY, cs.PL 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper presents a software defense mechanism to mitigate control-flow hijacking attacks on embedded systems. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also likely as the paper proposes a compiler transformation technique to achieve intra-address space isolation on embedded systems. 
- cs.AR (Architecture) is relevant as the paper focuses on ARM processors and their limitations in terms of memory safety and type safety. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper deals with embedded systems and their control mechanisms, which can have physical consequences if compromised. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the paper discusses the limitations of C programming language in terms of memory safety and type safety, and proposes a compiler transformation technique to address these issues.
